                <head>No. 252<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>The financial aid extended to Europe in 1952–1954 was only part of a larger,
                    broader program of mutual security assistance that spanned the globe before,
                    during, and after this period. In the following pages the editors have attempted
                    to present documentation on the Mutual Security Program that is nearly or
                    exclusively European in orientation, leaving to presentation in the general
                    mutual security compilation in <ref target="frus1952-54v01p1">volume I, Part
                        1</ref>, those documents dealing with European aid in the broad context of
                    global mutual security. However, some overlap inevitably remains and the reader
                    is urged to consult both the general and regional mutual security compilations
                    in order to obtain the maximum documentary information and perspective.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
